From d20751a4aeaedd53a2e5ba1a73ffbc46746cb9b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude Phase 1 <phase1@local>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 13:55:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 1: autonomous 911 call generator

- Replaces 'Deploy Incident' UI with 'Answer 911 Call' button + call-text display
- Adds INCIDENT_TYPES table (8 call types: hit-and-run, carjacking, suspicious vehicle, bike snatcher, foot robber, group of youths, person in distress, shots fired)
- Each call: weighted incident pick + random color (per-object-type weighted dist), direction, address, landmark
- Spawns BadGuy at random map point via existing placeBadGuy plumbing
- Reads call script aloud via SpeechSynthesis with randomized English voice
- Stashes incident metadata on badGuy for Phase 2/3 consumption (label, color, subkind, motion, callText)
- Stills motion for 'still' incidents (distress, shots fired, suspicious vehicle)
- Brightens 'Un' in 'Boston Uncommon' logo (color, weight, glow)
- Reset handler now clears call-display and tolerates removed tpicker element
